  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dda \u0d9c\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dcf \u0db6\u0dda\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The two Russians who were swept away in the sea are rescued",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Hikkaduwa Police said that two Russian nationals who were caught in a stream while swimming in the Hikkaduwa Panangoda Sea, were rescued by night police lifeguards and Navy lifeguards.",
        "The two rescued Russian foreigners are 27 and 29 years old.",
        "The two were staying at a tourist hotel in Hikkaduwa area and came to Hikkaduwa Panangoda beach yesterday afternoon for swimming.",
        "While they were swimming in the ocean, they got caught in a current and were swept into the sea about 800 meters deep."
      ],
